VALUES
(40, 13, 12, 43, 15, 2, 5, 'whosoever hath, to him shall be given', 'Abundance and Fruitfulness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the principle of receiving more when one is fruitful or has abundance. Matthew highlights that those who have will receive more, while John illustrates that branches that bear fruit are pruned to produce even more. This connection underscores the theme of growth and productivity in faith.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 12, 40, 21, 43, 43, 'whosoever hath not', 'Connection of Abundance and Loss', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of loss and gain in relation to the kingdom of God. The first passage suggests that those who have will receive more, while the second indicates that the kingdom will be taken from those who do not produce fruit.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 12, 66, 2, 5, 5, 'whosoever hath not', 'Abundance and Removal Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of loss and gain. Both passages emphasize that what one has can be taken away if not maintained, reflecting a principle of accountability.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 13, 26, 12, 2, 2, NULL, 'Seeing and Hearing Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the inability of the people to see and hear despite having the faculties to do so. This connection highlights a theme of spiritual blindness and deafness in the context of rebellion.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 13, 24, 5, 21, 21, NULL, 'Connection of Perception and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the lack of understanding among people who have the ability to see and hear. They highlight a spiritual blindness and deafness that prevents true comprehension.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 13, 23, 42, 18, 20, 'seeing see not; and hearing they hear not', 'Blindness and Deafness Motif', 'Both passages emphasize the themes of blindness and deafness. Matthew highlights the inability to understand despite seeing and hearing, while Isaiah calls out the deaf and blind, questioning their lack of perception.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 13, 47, 4, 3, 4, 'see not; and hearing they hear not', 'Spiritual Blindness and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the inability to see and understand spiritual truths. Matthew highlights the lack of understanding among the people, while 2 Corinthians speaks of minds being blinded, preventing belief in the gospel.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 13, 5, 29, 3, 4, NULL, 'Perception and Understanding in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize a lack of perception and understanding among the people. Matthew highlights the inability to see and hear, while Deuteronomy notes that the Lord has not given them a heart to perceive.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 13, 40, 13, 16, 16, 'seeing see not; and hearing they hear not', 'Seeing and Hearing Connection', 'This connection highlights the contrast between those who do not understand and those who are blessed with sight and hearing. Both passages emphasize the importance of perception and understanding in receiving the message.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 13, 43, 3, 19, 20, 'see not; and hearing they hear not', 'Connection of Light and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of spiritual blindness and the rejection of light. In Matthew, the inability to understand is highlighted, while John contrasts this with the love of darkness over light due to evil deeds.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 14, 23, 6, 9, 10, 'By hearing ye shall hear, and shall not understand', 'Connection of Hearing and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hearing without understanding and seeing without perceiving. This connection highlights the spiritual blindness and deafness of the people addressed in both texts.', 'theme', 0.8319999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 14, 26, 12, 2, 2, NULL, 'Rebellion and Spiritual Blindness', 'Both passages emphasize a spiritual condition where people have the ability to see and hear but fail to understand or perceive the truth. This connection highlights the theme of rebellion against divine revelation.', 'theme', 0.552, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 14, 47, 3, 14, 14, 'shall not understand; and seeing ye shall see', 'Spiritual Blindness and Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of spiritual blindness and lack of understanding among the people. Matthew highlights the inability to perceive the truth, while 2 Corinthians speaks of a veil that prevents comprehension of the old testament, which is removed in Christ.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 14, 42, 8, 10, 10, 'hearing ye shall hear, and shall not understand; and seeing ye shall see, and shall not perceive', 'Connection of Perception and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hearing and seeing without understanding. They illustrate how knowledge of the kingdom is given selectively, highlighting the mystery of divine revelation.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 14, 44, 28, 25, 27, 'By hearing ye shall hear, and shall not understand; and seeing ye shall see, and shall not perceive:', 'Connection of Prophetic Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hearing and not understanding, as well as seeing and not perceiving. They both reference the prophecy of Esaias, highlighting the spiritual blindness of the people.', 'prophecy', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 14, 41, 4, 12, 12, 'By hearing ye shall hear, and shall not understand; and seeing ye shall see, and shall not perceive:', 'Connection of Prophetic Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hearing and seeing without understanding or perceiving. They reflect a prophetic fulfillment regarding the spiritual blindness of the people.', 'prophecy', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 14, 43, 12, 39, 40, 'the prophecy of Esaias', 'Connection of Prophetic Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of spiritual blindness and lack of understanding. They reference the prophecy of Esaias, highlighting how people hear and see but do not comprehend.', 'prophecy', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 15, 23, 6, 10, 10, 'see with their eyes, and hear with their ears', 'Connection of Heart and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the dullness of the people''s hearts and senses, highlighting a spiritual blindness and inability to understand. The phrases about seeing, hearing, and understanding are nearly identical, reinforcing the theme of spiritual resistance to divine revelation.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 15, 38, 7, 11, 11, NULL, 'Hearing and Understanding Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the refusal to hear and understand. Matthew highlights the closing of ears and eyes, while Zechariah describes stopping ears to avoid hearing.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 15, 41, 4, 12, 12, 'see with their eyes, and hear with their ears', 'Connection of Spiritual Blindness', 'Both passages emphasize the inability to perceive spiritual truths. They highlight the condition of the heart and senses that prevents understanding and conversion.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 15, 43, 8, 43, 44, 'dull of hearing', 'Understanding and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the inability to hear and understand spiritual truths. Matthew highlights the closed hearts and dull ears of the people, while John addresses the failure to understand Jesus'' words, linking it to their spiritual lineage.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 15, 55, 2, 25, 26, 'understand with their heart', 'Heart and Understanding Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the need for understanding and repentance. Matthew highlights the closing of eyes and ears, while 2 Timothy speaks of acknowledging the truth to recover from deception.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 15, 23, 29, 10, 12, 'their ears are dull of hearing', 'Spiritual Blindness and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of spiritual blindness and dullness of hearing. In Matthew, the people''s hearts are described as ''waxed gross,'' while Isaiah speaks of the Lord closing their eyes, indicating a similar condition of unresponsiveness to divine revelation.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 15, 24, 17, 14, 14, 'I should heal them', 'Healing and Understanding Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of healing. In Matthew, healing is contingent upon understanding and conversion, while Jeremiah directly requests healing from the Lord.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 16, 42, 10, 23, 24, 'Blessed are your eyes, for they see', 'Blessed Eyes and Ears Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of blessedness associated with seeing and hearing divine truths. Both passages emphasize the privilege of the disciples in perceiving what many prophets and kings longed to see and hear.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 16, 49, 1, 17, 18, 'blessed are your eyes, for they see', 'Blessed Eyes and Enlightened Understanding', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual perception. Both passages emphasize the importance of seeing and understanding divine truths, with Matthew focusing on the blessedness of seeing and hearing, while Ephesians speaks of the enlightenment of the eyes of understanding.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 16, 40, 16, 17, 17, 'blessed are your eyes, for they see', 'Blessings of Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of divine revelation and the blessing that comes from seeing and hearing spiritual truths. In Matthew 13:16, the blessedness of seeing and hearing is highlighted, while in Matthew 16:17, the revelation of truth to Peter is attributed to God, reinforcing the idea of spiritual insight as a divine gift.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 16, 43, 20, 29, 29, 'blessed are your eyes, for they see', 'Blessed are the Believers', 'This connection highlights the theme of blessing associated with seeing and believing. Both passages emphasize the value of faith, with Matthew noting the blessing of those who see and hear, while John extends this blessing to those who believe without seeing.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 16, 44, 26, 18, 18, 'your eyes, for they see', 'Seeing and Turning to Light', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of seeing and understanding spiritual truths. Matthew highlights the blessing of seeing and hearing, while Acts speaks to opening eyes and turning from darkness to light.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
